attributes.title: Why Are You Here? - Episode 1
attributes.caption: Why are you here?
attributes.description: Several strangers wake up to find themselves in a mysterious suburban neighborhood.
attributes.display_title: S1:E1 - Why Are You Here? - Episode 1

attributes.title: The One With The Premise - Episode 2
attributes.caption: The One With The Premise
attributes.description: Everybody finds a note telling him or her to go to the house that Wade and Sam are inhabiting.
attributes.display_title: S1:E2 - The One With The Premise - Episode 2

attributes.title: We Have a Floater - Episode 3
attributes.caption: We Have a Floater
attributes.description: To replace the recently deceased goldfish, the house gets a new goldfish in addition to the ones remaining in the tank.
attributes.display_title: S1:E3 - We Have a Floater - Episode 3

attributes.title: Sublimination Round - Episode 4
attributes.caption: Sublimination Round
attributes.description: The Omnipotent Voice orders Sam, Wade, and Tovar to compete against Catherine, Dr. Chalmers, and Dutchmiller in a contest to cook and eat grilled cheese sandwiches.

attributes.title: Things Misremembered - Episode 5
attributes.caption: Things Misremembered
attributes.description: Wade and Tovar report to Sam and Dr. Chalmers that somebody was murdered while they were swimming in the pool.

attributes.title: Idol Desperation - Episode 6
attributes.caption: Idol Desperation
attributes.description: Sam, Wade, and Chalmers call everyone else to tell the news of the death.

attributes.title: Star-Crossed Suckers - Episode 7
attributes.caption: Star-Crossed Suckers
attributes.description: Sam looks through his telescope and notices that the constellations are incorrect.

attributes.title: WSI - Episode 8
attributes.caption: WSI
attributes.description: Sam and Dr. Chalmers speculate where Strangerhood Lane is located. For unfounded reasons, Dr. Chalmers believes that they are in Cleveland, Ohio.

attributes.title: Detective Defective - Episode 9
attributes.caption: Detective Defective
attributes.description: Wade finds a pre-built police station and assumes the role of detective. Almost immediately, he sets to work, trying to find clues to solve the murder on Strangerhood Lane.

attributes.title: Devil May Care - Episode 10
attributes.caption: Devil May Care
attributes.description: As Griggs realizes that he is a wanted man, he gets into a car that he finds. But, first, he stops to consider his options, unaware that a garden gnome is in the seat next to his.

attributes.title: Cell Block Duh - Episode 11
attributes.caption: Cell Block Duh
attributes.description: In a prison cell Griggs meets Tovar and Dutchmiller, acting as his lawyer.

attributes.title: Surprise Guest - Episode 12
attributes.caption: Surprise Guest
attributes.description: Dutchmiller hosts his own late night show.

attributes.title: Nikki's Alias - Episode 14
attributes.caption: Nikki's Alias
attributes.description: A ghost from the grave reveals the truth behind the murder.

attributes.title: Lost in Place - Episode 15
attributes.caption: Lost in Place
attributes.description: While attempting to discover what the hell is going on, the inhabitants of Strangerhood Lane get lost.

attributes.title: The Montage Exposition - Episode 16
attributes.caption: The Montage Exposition
attributes.description: After scolding the mysterious man for being overly dramatic about the possibility of getting fired, everybody begins to question who he is.

attributes.title: The Final Countdown - Episode 17
attributes.caption: The Final Countdown
attributes.description: In the final episode of the series the residents of Strangerhood Lane finally get to go home.
